      <h1
        class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-neutral-900 sm:text-5xl gsap-fade-in"
      >
        Fullstack developer, indiehacker & background in business.
      </h1>
      <div class="mt-6 space-y-7 text-base text-neutral-800 gsap-fade-in">
        <p>
          I have a varied background spanning from a masters degree in business,
          doing consulting, technical sales at Microsoft and co-founding
          easywave.io. On the evenings and weekend I've been doing side projects
          both as a hobby and as an indiehacker.
        </p>
        <p>
          A general theme is that I've been drawn to technical topics and have
          taken large steps towards more technical depth. Starting my journey
          with low code, which out of frustration with the limitations lead me
          to learning web development. After spending time in React-land with
          using tech-twitter's recommended solutions I desired to learn more
          fundamental programming and technologies. Now I'm on a mission of
          becoming the best full stack developer I can be.
        </p>
        <p>
          I'm a product-oriented developer with a strong passion for
          understanding the problem to be solved. In projects I encourage
          experimenting, testing hypotheses and being aware of assumptions.
        </p>
        <p>
          I have many hobbies and love to stay active. I do CrossFit to get in
          better shape, love to run, rock climb and hike mountains or do walks
          by the sea. I've learned to enjoy reading. Books are now one of my
          favorite ways of learning technical topics and I read fiction to wind
          down.
        </p>
      </div>
